The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 05 November is 6,340 (733.8 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 31 October, there were 804 new confirmed cases (93.1 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 24 October, there were 707 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 14% ( 97 extra cases).
